    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>IN BRIEF: Education; BONDS FOR CONSTRUCTION PROJECTS APPROVED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Merri Rosenberg</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rosenberg, Merri</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Voters in Eastchester, NY, approve $12.4 million bond issue for renovation and expansion of elementary schools; Harrison voters approve $1.044 million bond for eight-classroom modular unit at middle school (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Eastchester and Harrison voters have approved bonds for construction projects. In Eastchester, a $12.4 million bond was passed, 1,260 to 592, for renovations and expansions in the district's elementary schools. The bonds will cost the average taxpayer $90 a year starting in 2003-2004. In Harrison, the vote was 1,563 to 697 for a $1.044 million bond to provide an eight-classroom modular unit at the Louis M. Klein Middle School. During the three-year life of the bond, the average homeowner will see a tax increase of about $26 annually.</p>
        <p>Merri Rosenberg</p>
      </block>
